    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Francis H. Drake writes that they are sending from Leominster about eight dollars worth of articles and also one dollar in money from Mrs. Smith. Francis H. Drake &quot;has promised Mrs. Kimball she should have our things for her table if she took one. Please dispose of these accordingly.&quot; She introduces Miss Maria C. Richardson and Miss Elizabeth Blodgett, who will be happy to assist Maria Weston Chapman in any way she thinks best.</subfield>
